   "notes": "<strong>4. Size of <a href=\"http://www.aplustopper.com/nucleus-of-atom/\">Nucleus</a></strong> If R is the radius of the nucleus having mass number A, then<br>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-175111 jetpack-lazy-image\" src=\"https://i1.wp.com/www.cbselabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Nuclei-Class-12-Notes-Chapter-13-Img-2.png?resize=220%2C304&amp;ssl=1\" alt=\"Nuclei Class 12 Notes Chapter 13 Img 2\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" data-lazy-srcset=\"https://i1.wp.com/www.cbselabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Nuclei-Class-12-Notes-Chapter-13-Img-2.png?w=220&amp;ssl=1 220w, https://i1.wp.com/www.cbselabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Nuclei-Class-12-Notes-Chapter-13-Img-2.png?resize=217%2C300&amp;ssl=1 217w\" data-lazy-sizes=\"(max-width: 220px) 100vw, 220px\" data-lazy-src=\"https://i1.wp.com/www.cbselabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Nuclei-Class-12-Notes-Chapter-13-Img-2.png?resize=220%2C304&amp;is-pending-load=1#038;ssl=1\" srcset=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7\" width=\"220\" height=\"304\"><noscript><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-175111\" src=\"https://i1.wp.com/www.cbselabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Nuclei-Class-12-Notes-Chapter-13-Img-2.png?resize=220%2C304&amp;ssl=1\" alt=\"Nuclei Class 12 Notes Chapter 13 Img 2\" srcset=\"https://i1.wp.com/www.cbselabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Nuclei-Class-12-Notes-Chapter-13-Img-2.png?w=220&amp;ssl=1 220w, https://i1.wp.com/www.cbselabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Nuclei-Class-12-Notes-Chapter-13-Img-2.png?resize=217%2C300&amp;ssl=1 217w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 220px) 100vw, 220px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" width=\"220\" height=\"304\"></noscript><br>\n<strong>5. Nuclear Density</strong> Density of nuclear matter is the ratio of mass of nucleus and its volume.<br>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-175112 jetpack-lazy-image\" src=\"https://i1.wp.com/www.cbselabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Nuclei-Class-12-Notes-Chapter-13-Img-3.png?resize=494%2C376&amp;ssl=1\" alt=\"Nuclei Class 12 Notes Chapter 13 Img 3\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" data-lazy-srcset=\"https://i1.wp.com/www.cbselabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Nuclei-Class-12-Notes-Chapter-13-Img-3.png?w=494&amp;ssl=1 494w, https://i1.wp.com/www.cbselabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Nuclei-Class-12-Notes-Chapter-13-Img-3.png?resize=300%2C228&amp;ssl=1 300w\" data-lazy-sizes=\"(max-width: 494px) 100vw, 494px\" data-lazy-src=\"https://i1.wp.com/www.cbselabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Nuclei-Class-12-Notes-Chapter-13-Img-3.png?resize=494%2C376&amp;is-pending-load=1#038;ssl=1\" srcset=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7\" width=\"494\" height=\"376\"><noscript><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-175112\" src=\"https://i1.wp.com/www.cbselabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Nuclei-Class-12-Notes-Chapter-13-Img-3.png?resize=494%2C376&amp;ssl=1\" alt=\"Nuclei Class 12 Notes Chapter 13 Img 3\" srcset=\"https://i1.wp.com/www.cbselabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Nuclei-Class-12-Notes-Chapter-13-Img-3.png?w=494&amp;ssl=1 494w, https://i1.wp.com/www.cbselabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Nuclei-Class-12-Notes-Chapter-13-Img-3.png?resize=300%2C228&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 494px) 100vw, 494px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" width=\"494\" height=\"376\"></noscript><br>\n<strong>6. Radioactivity</strong> It is the phenomenon of spontaneous disintegration of the nucleus of an atom with emission of one or more radiations like α-particle, β-particle or γ-rays.<br>\n<strong>7. Radioactive Decay</strong> It is a nuclear transformation process in which the radioactive rays are emitted from the nucleus of the atom. This process cannot be accelerated and slow down by any physical or chemical process."
