   "notes": "<strong>8. Radioactivity Decay Law</strong> According to this law, the rate of decay of radioactive atoms at any instant is proportional to the number of atoms present at that instant.<br>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-175113 jetpack-lazy-image\" src=\"https://i2.wp.com/www.cbselabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Nuclei-Class-12-Notes-Chapter-13-Img-4.png?resize=347%2C326&amp;ssl=1\" alt=\"Nuclei Class 12 Notes Chapter 13 Img 4\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" data-lazy-srcset=\"https://i2.wp.com/www.cbselabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Nuclei-Class-12-Notes-Chapter-13-Img-4.png?w=347&amp;ssl=1 347w, https://i2.wp.com/www.cbselabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Nuclei-Class-12-Notes-Chapter-13-Img-4.png?resize=300%2C282&amp;ssl=1 300w\" data-lazy-sizes=\"(max-width: 347px) 100vw, 347px\" data-lazy-src=\"https://i2.wp.com/www.cbselabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Nuclei-Class-12-Notes-Chapter-13-Img-4.png?resize=347%2C326&amp;is-pending-load=1#038;ssl=1\" srcset=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7\" width=\"347\" height=\"326\"><noscript><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-175113\" src=\"https://i2.wp.com/www.cbselabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Nuclei-Class-12-Notes-Chapter-13-Img-4.png?resize=347%2C326&amp;ssl=1\" alt=\"Nuclei Class 12 Notes Chapter 13 Img 4\" srcset=\"https://i2.wp.com/www.cbselabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Nuclei-Class-12-Notes-Chapter-13-Img-4.png?w=347&amp;ssl=1 347w, https://i2.wp.com/www.cbselabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Nuclei-Class-12-Notes-Chapter-13-Img-4.png?resize=300%2C282&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 347px) 100vw, 347px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" width=\"347\" height=\"326\"></noscript><br>\n<strong>9. Half-life</strong> Half-life of a radioactive element is defined as the time during which half the number of atoms present initially in the sample of the element decay.<br>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-175114 jetpack-lazy-image\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.cbselabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Nuclei-Class-12-Notes-Chapter-13-Img-5.png?resize=569%2C313&amp;ssl=1\" alt=\"Nuclei Class 12 Notes Chapter 13 Img 5\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" data-lazy-srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.cbselabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Nuclei-Class-12-Notes-Chapter-13-Img-5.png?w=569&amp;ssl=1 569w, https://i0.wp.com/www.cbselabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Nuclei-Class-12-Notes-Chapter-13-Img-5.png?resize=300%2C165&amp;ssl=1 300w\" data-lazy-sizes=\"(max-width: 569px) 100vw, 569px\" data-lazy-src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.cbselabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Nuclei-Class-12-Notes-Chapter-13-Img-5.png?resize=569%2C313&amp;is-pending-load=1#038;ssl=1\" srcset=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAIBRAA7\" width=\"569\" height=\"313\"><noscript><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-175114\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.cbselabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Nuclei-Class-12-Notes-Chapter-13-Img-5.png?resize=569%2C313&amp;ssl=1\" alt=\"Nuclei Class 12 Notes Chapter 13 Img 5\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.cbselabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Nuclei-Class-12-Notes-Chapter-13-Img-5.png?w=569&amp;ssl=1 569w, https://i0.wp.com/www.cbselabs.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Nuclei-Class-12-Notes-Chapter-13-Img-5.png?resize=300%2C165&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 569px) 100vw, 569px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" width=\"569\" height=\"313\"></noscript>"
