   "notes": "<strong>14.</strong> The SI unit of radioactivity is Becquerel (B<sub>q</sub>).<br>\n1 Becquerel(B<sub>q</sub>) = 1 disintegration/second Other units<br>\n<strong>(i) Curie</strong> The activity of a radioactive sample is said to be one curie.<br>\n1 curie (Ci) = 3.7 x 10<sup>10</sup> decays/second<br>\n<strong>(ii) Rutherford</strong> The activity of a radioactive sample is said to be one rutherford.<br>\n1 rutherford (Rd) = 10<sup>6</sup> decays/second"
